<br>
However, I noticed an unfortunate trend.  For 48 levels with my Beastlord, whenever I duoed with another pet class I could step into melee range and whack the mob with impunity once the pets had several seconds to build aggro.  This only applied if there were two or more pets on the mob.  Last night, however, the moment I stepped into aggro range (barring the mob being stunned by the pets), it would turn and attack me.  Proved and re-proved over a 7-hour session: pets holding aggro with more than two seems to have been nerfed.  I would get pounded into Iksar Goo repeatedly by these mobs that double-hit for 120-150 points the moment I stepped into aggro range.<br>
<br>
Now, I am willing to suspect that maybe it has something to dow with my level and the level of the mobs now.  Would any younger Beastlords be willing to duo with another pet class and test this situation?  Sic two pets on the mob, wait 5 seconds, and step into aggro range and start whacking.  See if you get aggro right off the bat.  I would really, really hope that this is simply a higher-level phenomenon I am observing rather than a pet nerf by Verant.<br>
<br>
