That's true IF THERE IS ONLY ONE PET.<br>
<br>
(This has been repeated so many times, yet people don't read the thread...)<br>
<br>
If there were two pets on a mob, then normal aggro rules would apply and the pets could (*not* neccesarily would) hold aggro over a PC in melee range.  If the PC laid on a DoT, a debuff, and did a lot of damage (or used his Taunt a lot) he could still get aggro over two pets, but normally would not.<br>
