<br>
I duoed with my chanter friend for about an hour last night, I was (am) lvl 25, he lvl 24. We where in LOIO and he pulled sarnaks/gobbos/whatnot and we let the mob hit him once so his pet would jump in, then I siced my pet and jumped in right away.<br>
I had aggro for about 5 seconds or so then the mob turned to my or the chanter pet and started pounding on them.<br>
<br>
However, the chanter pet stole aggro away every now and then, and it doesnt hit all that hard, so its not impossible that they changed the ammount of taunt warders get.. Either that or chanter pets has a extremly good taunt skill, which isnt so unlikely considering that their pet is mostly there to get a mob off their master so he can flee (or nowadays, mez).<br>
<br>
